HEADWORD: hoactzin
<hw>hoactzin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A crested ill-smelling South
American bird (<spn>Opisthocomus hoazin</spn>) whose young have claws on
the first and second digits of the wings.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hoatzin, stinkbird, <spn>Opisthocomus
hoazin</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

